   Output: id, content, (paradedb.score(id))
   ->  Custom Scan (ParadeDB Scan) on public.test_docs  (cost=10.00..10.01 rows=1 width=40) (actual time=0.608..0.609 rows=1 loops=1)
         Output: id, content, paradedb.score(id)
         Table: test_docs
         Index: test_docs_idx
         Segment Count: 1
         Heap Fetches: 1
         Virtual Tuples: 0
         Invisible Tuples: 0
         Exec Method: TopNScanExecState
         Scores: true
            Sort Field: paradedb.score()
            Sort Direction: desc
            Top N Limit: 1
         Tantivy Query: {"with_index":{"query":{"parse_with_field":{"field":"content","query_string":"document","lenient":null,"conjunction_mode":null}}}}
         Human Readable Query: content:(document)
 Planning Time: 2.516 ms
 Execution Time: 0.814 ms
(19 rows)

